ADF: 0.1

🎯 TASK: Codebase analysis subsystem development context

📋 CONTEXT:
  - packages: blast (reverse dependency graph + BFS blast radius), surface (route + D1 schema extraction)
  - Both packages are zero-dependency: no @stackbilt/types, no runtime deps at all
  - Both are deterministic: no LLM calls, no AST — regex-based scanning for universality
  - CLI command handlers in packages/cli/src/commands/blast.ts and surface.ts
  - Feed governance signals: blast radius ≥20 files → CROSS_CUTTING warning

⚠ CONSTRAINTS [load-bearing]:
  - blast and surface commands must support --format json for stable machine output
  - blast: --root and --depth flags must be in VALUE_FLAGS to avoid positional sweep
  - blast must handle ESM .js → .ts rewrite, tsconfig extends chains, src/index.* fallback
  - surface must strip block and line comments before route scanning (jsdoc false positives)
  - surface must ignore __tests__, __mocks__, __fixtures__, *.test.*, *.spec.* files
  - Route detection requires path to start with / to avoid matching list.post(item) etc.
  - blastRadius BFS must track visited set to handle import cycles without infinite loop
  - Exit codes: 0 success, 1 reserved for future governance thresholds, 2 usage error

